{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"7381c6c5-21ad-43a8-87ea-bb891a73f492","content":"With **MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0**, Microsoft.Testing.Platform is already the default runner. You just need to:\n\n1. **Remove (or delete) the `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>`** property from your project file. That single property is what forces the legacy VSTest runner.\n\n2. **Review your test invocation.** `dotnet test` still works, but the underlying runner changes. If you run the test binary directly (`./YourTests.exe`), you'll get the new platform's CLI — use `--help` to see available options.\n\n3. **Migrate any `.runsettings` usage.** The new platform uses its own configuration; some VSTest-specific runsettings keys may need updating or replacement with `[assembly: Parallelize]` attributes or MSBuild properties.\n\n4. **Update CI scripts** — the exit codes and console output format differ slightly, and some VSTest-specific switches (e.g., `--logger trx`) become `--report-trx`.\n\n**Minimal diff:**\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n-   <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\nThat's it for the project file — the SDK handles the rest.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8090b926-1bcf-46b8-ba4c-21df2a4d41b9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.\n\nWhen using MSTest.Sdk, switching from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform involves a few key changes:\n\n1. Remove `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` from the project file (or set it to `false`). In MSTest.Sdk 3.8.0, the default runner is Microsoft.Testing.Platform, so simply removing the `UseVSTest` property should switch you over.\n\n\n2. The CLI commands remain largely the same with `dotnet test`, though you can also run the test executable directly if needed.\n3. Test configuration through runsettings files may require some adjustments to work with the new platform.","outputTokens":559,"requestId":"CFE9:237CD0:618666E:6CBEAC2:69EC0F05"},"id":"6f02b40a-bc39-48f5-be7d-a42675743f71","timestamp":"2026-04-25T00:47:14.100Z","parentId":"d689978e-fe51-4fb2-89dd-99d4d8e0eebf"}
